summary:
In one form or another, we all give and take feedback from everyone around us. We form our impressions of others, and our reputation gradually develops. Recommendation letters are the formal version of such feedback mechanism.
I would like to support my students where possible. However, &hellip;
1 .Should you ask me for a letter of recommendation or should I be on your referee list? Strongest recommendation letters for you would be penned by faculty who know you well and can speak to your abilities above and beyond the standard coursework.
